{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770316484,"nonce":"13iJY+LCfCAUIWBTqWxC8WJg1xk=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87ooos-","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/167","origin":"github"},"title":"Add CODE_MAP.md for quick project discovery (project config pattern)","message":"## Problem\n\nAI agents need quick access to critical project information (GitHub URLs, key paths, package locations) when working with uninitialized workspaces or debugging repository discovery issues.\n\n**Recent Example**: When asked to check PRs/issues for `unh_marine_autonomy`, the agent had difficulty because:\n1. Workspace not initialized (broken `layers/` symlink)\n2. GitHub owner unknown (guessed `UNH-Robotics` instead of `rolker`)\n3. No quick reference map - had to grep through docs to find URLs\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nAdd a **CODE_MAP.md** file to provide a \"cheat sheet\" with critical information:\n\n```markdown\n# Code Map - Quick Reference\n\n## GitHub Repository\n- **Owner**: rolker\n- **Repo**: unh_marine_autonomy\n- **URL**: https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy\n- **Branch**: jazzy\n\n## Key Paths (after workspace init)\n- **Key Repo**: `layers/main/core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy/`\n- **Layer Configs**: `layers/main/core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy/config/repos/`\n- **Packages**: \n  - mission_manager/\n  - helm_manager/\n  - command_bridge/\n\n## Related Repos\n- marine_ais: https://github.com/rolker/marine_ais\n- unh_marine_navigation: https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_navigation\n```\n\n## Location (Project-Specific Config)\n\nFollowing the workspace/project separation pattern (#132), this should be:\n\n**Project-level**: `unh_marine_autonomy/config/CODE_MAP.md` (in the key repository)\n- Committed to the `unh_marine_autonomy` repo\n- Available at `layers/main/core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy/config/CODE_MAP.md` after initialization\n\n**NOT workspace-level** - This contains project-specific information (GitHub URLs, package names, etc.)\n\n## Integration Points\n\n1. **GLOSSARY.md** (#102) - Reference CODE_MAP.md for quick lookups\n2. **Architecture Separation** (#132) - Follows project/workspace config pattern\n3. **Status Report** - Could parse CODE_MAP.md to show GitHub info\n4. **Agent Instructions** - Reference CODE_MAP.md as first-look resource\n\n## Benefits\n\n- ✅ **Fast discovery** - One file with all critical paths/URLs\n- ✅ **Uninitialized workspace support** - Can find GitHub info before `make bootstrap`\n- ✅ **Reduces agent confusion** - No need to grep for repository details\n- ✅ **Follows architecture pattern** - Project config stays in project repo\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] Create `unh_marine_autonomy/config/CODE_MAP.md` template\n- [ ] Document GitHub URLs, key paths, package structure\n- [ ] Add reference from workspace GLOSSARY.md (#102)\n- [ ] Update agent instructions to check CODE_MAP.md first\n- [ ] Consider parsing CODE_MAP.md in status_report.sh\n\n## Priority\n\nLow-Medium - Quality of life improvement for agent discovery\n\n## Related Issues\n\n- #102 - Project-specific glossary (similar pattern)\n- #132 - Workspace/project config separation (architectural alignment)\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}